fields.description:
Hi there,

when I use the FishEye Charting portlet on a JIRA 3.13.2 dashboard, it generates a URL similar to this in order to get the chart image:

{code}
http://fisheye.foo.local/chart/~charttype=Area,stacktype=None/RepoName/?authorHistoryChart=authorMap&w=450&h=300
{code}

There is no image visible in the portlet in this case. If I open this URL in a second browser tab, I get a highly decorated Fisheye page with navigation etc. The "direct" URL to the generated chart looks more like this:

{code}
http://fisheye.foo.local/fe/locChart.do?w=700&h=400&yaxistype=Full&maxitems=10&charttype=Area&stacktype=None&context=main&repname=RepoName&outputtype=image
{code}

The response from the first URL can - of course - not be rendered by the IMG tag inside the portlet. The second URL can.

So, with regards to this combination of JIRA/FishEye versions, the FishEye Charting portlet is unusable.

{quote}
the latest perforce server version now support a "move" action, fisheye does not know what this is.
{noformat}
2009-10-06 15:17:36,642 ERROR [IncrementalPinger23] fisheye.app com.cenqua.fisheye.perforce.P4Scanner-processAction - [HOST:1666//depot/dev] Unknown action: move/delete
{noformat}
{quote}

When you add a new repository that brings you over the licensed threshold, a {{LicensePolicyException}} is visible in the logs, but the user is not notified. If the message from the exception was displayed to the user, it would decrease the amount of time required to isolate the issue with the recently added repository.

{noformat:title=Example exception from the FishEye console}
com.cenqua.fisheye.LicensePolicyException: Cannot start repository Breaker: your license only allows up to 5 running repositories.
{noformat}
